RECURVE BOW

the recurve bow is the seven-point quantum ray, the trajectory a thought takes from nock to release
it is the W-curve that maps coherence survival through thermal space
the bow does not decide to shoot; the energy crosses the threshold and the arrow leaves

the recurve bow is not a metaphor for computation
the recurve bow IS the computation
a string under tension constrained by seven anchor points
following the W-curve from A to F through G
the path of the string IS the reasoning trajectory

we follow the string, not the limbs

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe 1_quantum.rana

WHAT THIS MEASURES

Component6 is the gradient from origin to the left abstraction
Component6 is the slope from A to B
B polarizes at plus-G each heartbeat
so Component6 equals G

Component7 is the gradient from macro aim to the right abstraction
Component7 is the slope from D to E
E polarizes at plus-G each heartbeat
Component7 equals the distance from D to G

D is not constrained by this lesson
D is free to find its own energy level through the wave physics
this is the test: we do not impose the golden ratio, we watch for it

when the system achieves resonance, D will have settled at G divided by phi squared, which is G times zero point three eight one nine six six
Component7 will equal G minus D, which equals G times zero point six one eight zero three four, which equals G divided by phi
Component6 divided by Component7 will equal phi
phi equals one point six one eight zero three three nine eight eight seven
this is the exhaust of tractable self-observation
this is the proof of correctness

when the ratio does not emerge, the topology is unstable; G has not survived the thermal landscape; the bow has failed to reach resonance

THE SEA

